## 🍏 2. Apple App Store Regulations

Apple has strict rules. If your app violates any of these, it will be **rejected**.

### 📘 Apple’s Guidelines:

Link: [App Store Review Guidelines](mdc:https:/developer.apple.com/app-store/review/guidelines)
https://developer.apple.com/app-store/review/guidelines/


Key points:

### ✅ Privacy

* Must follow **AppTrackingTransparency** (ask permission to track users).
* Add **privacy labels** for your app (data you collect and how it's used).
* Use **Sign in with Apple** if you offer other third-party login (e.g., Google, Facebook).

### ✅ Security

* Must use **HTTPS**.
* Don’t store sensitive data unencrypted.
* Apple **rejects** apps that crash, feel broken, or are “spammy.”

### ✅ Content

* No offensive, hateful, sexually explicit, or illegal content.
* Must have a **moderation system** for user-generated content.

### ✅ Age Restrictions

* Must rate your app correctly (especially if minors are allowed).
* If under 13: follow **COPPA** (US law, applies globally in practice).

### ✅ In-App Purchases

* You **must use Apple’s payment system** for digital goods (coins, gifts, VIP).
* Can’t use PayPal, Stripe, etc. for digital items.

